@node "8_10" " SECTION 8 - Essence Settings and Other Attributes "
@{b}@{i} 10] Marble, By Rob Freundlich@{ub}@{ui}

Make your object a pale white (190-ish on all the RGB sliders), high Shiny value, high Hardness, low Roughness, Specular just a few shades below the object color, ummm, possibly others as well.

Apply two wood textures.  The textures are rotated with respect to each other. Both have very wide bands (and a low number of bands) and a large Variation value (for "burl" effect, according to Understanding Imagine). The color of each texture is a darker shade of grey than the object, and the two textures have slightly different colors.

